    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-26T12:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-26T12:41:00-05:00" n="361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123G31/110</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-26T18:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.22 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2207. Spanish Embassy, Berlin, states German authorities have ordered Knauer
                    (warehouseman) to deliver to them seven boxes said to contain gold and
                    silverware belonging to former Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GJW2"
                        >Gerard</persName>. Knauer has been instructed not to deliver cases without
                    authorization of Spanish Embassy, and protest against this seizure has been sent
                    to German Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
